<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Resources on Jikkou</title><link>https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/kafka-connect/resources/</link><description>Recent content in Resources on Jikkou</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/kafka-connect/resources/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>KafkaConnectors</title><link>https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/kafka-connect/resources/connector/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/kafka-connect/resources/connector/</guid><description>&lt;div class="pageinfo pageinfo-info">
&lt;p>This section describes the resource definition format for &lt;code>KafkaConnector&lt;/code> entities, which can be used to define the
configuration and status of connectors you plan to create and manage on specific Kafka Connect clusters.&lt;/p>

&lt;/div>

&lt;h2 id="definition-format-of-kafkaconnector">Definition Format of &lt;code>KafkaConnector&lt;/code>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Below is the overall structure of the &lt;code>KafkaConnector&lt;/code> resource.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nn">---&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">apiVersion&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;kafka.jikkou.io/v1beta1&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The api version (required)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">kind&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;KafkaConnector&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The resource kind (required)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">metadata&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">name&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;string&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The name of the connector (required)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">labels&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># Name of the Kafka Connect cluster to create the connector instance in (required).&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">kafka.jikkou.io/connect-cluster&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;string&amp;gt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">annotations&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># Override client properties to connect to Kafka Connect cluster (optional).&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">jikkou.io/config-override&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">| &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;json&amp;gt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">spec&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">connectorClass&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;string&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># Name or alias of the class for this connector.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">tasksMax&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;integer&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The maximum number of tasks for the Kafka Connector.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">config&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># Configuration properties of the connector.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">&amp;lt;key&amp;gt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;value&amp;gt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">state&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;string&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The state the connector should be in. Defaults to running.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>See below for details about all these fields.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>